The photoluminescence quantum yields (ΦF
                        ) of FP1 and FP2 were determined, at 25 °C, according to the traditional method [48,49], using ﬂuorescein as standard [50]. To minimize reabsorption effects, the absorbance’s sample values were kept below 0.1 [51]. The photoluminescence quantum yields (ΦF
                        ) of FP1 and FP2 are 0.77 and 0.51 respectively.(Table 3
                        )
